pheatmap.colorsymmetric <- function(x,lim=NULL,...)
{
    require(pheatmap)
    if(is.null(lim)){
        lim <- max(abs(x), na.rm=TRUE)
        if( min(x, na.rm=TRUE) < 0 ){
            lim_down<- -lim
            col_palette<- colorRampPalette(c("blue","white","red"))(256)
        }else{        
            lim_down<- 0
            col_palette<- colorRampPalette(c("white","red"))(256)
        }
    }else{
        lim <- 1
        lim_down<- -1
        col_palette<- colorRampPalette(c("blue","white","red"))(256)        
    }
    pheatmap(
        x, color = col_palette,
        breaks=seq(lim_down,lim,length.out=255), ... )
}
# Function to generate correlation heatmaps between DESeq2 and GEDI
cor_heatmap<- function(lis_1, lis_2, celltypes_order, cutoff_col=NULL, cutoff_use=NULL, ...){
         
    intersect_genes<- intersect(rownames(lis_1[[1]]), rownames(lis_2[[1]]))
    
    cat("genes intersecting:", length(intersect_genes), "\n")

    for( i in 1:length(lis_1) ){
        lis_1[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_1[[i]])[intersect_genes,]
    }

    for( i in 1:length(lis_2) ){
        lis_2[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_2[[i]])[intersect_genes,,drop=F]
    }
    
    celltypes_use<- names(lis_1)

    celltypes_heatmap<- c()
   
    for( celltype_look in celltypes_use){
        ggdat<- cbind(lis_1[[celltype_look]], lis_2[[celltype_look]])
        if( !is.null(cutoff_use) ){
            ggdat<- ggdat[which(ggdat[,cutoff_col] < cutoff_use),] # remove genes with noisy DESeq estimates
            print(nrow(ggdat))
        }
        if(nrow(ggdat)>20){
            celltypes_heatmap<- c(celltype_look, celltypes_heatmap)
        }        
    }

    ## Heatmap
    mat_cor<- matrix(0, nrow=length(celltypes_heatmap), ncol=length(celltypes_heatmap))

    for( i in 1:length(celltypes_heatmap) ){
        for( j in 1:length(celltypes_heatmap)){
            celltype_i<- celltypes_heatmap[i]
            celltype_j<- celltypes_heatmap[j]
            ggdat<- cbind(lis_1[[celltype_i]], lis_2[[celltype_j]])
            if( !is.null(cutoff_use) ){        
                ggdat<- ggdat[which(ggdat[,cutoff_col] < cutoff_use),] # remove genes with noisy DESeq estimates
            }
            mat_cor[i,j]<- cor(ggdat$logFC, ggdat$gedi_log2FC)        
        }
    }

    rownames(mat_cor)<- colnames(mat_cor)<- celltypes_heatmap

    missing<- setdiff(celltypes_order, celltypes_heatmap)
    if (length(missing) > 0 ){
        cat("Missing cells:", setdiff(celltypes_order, celltypes_heatmap), "\n")
    }
    celltypes_order<- intersect(celltypes_order, celltypes_heatmap)

    return(mat_cor[celltypes_order, celltypes_order])    

}
# Function to generate correlation heatmaps between DESeq2 (cohort1) and DESeq2 (cohort2)
cor_heatmap_deseq<- function(lis_1, lis_2, celltypes_order_1, celltypes_order_2) {
    
    intersect_genes<- intersect(rownames(lis_1[[1]]), rownames(lis_2[[1]]))
    
    cat("genes intersecting:", length(intersect_genes), "\n")

    for( i in 1:length(lis_1) ){
        lis_1[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_1[[i]])[intersect_genes,]
    }

    for( i in 1:length(lis_2) ){
        lis_2[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_2[[i]])[intersect_genes,,drop=F]
    }

    celltypes_1<- names(lis_1)
    celltypes_2<- names(lis_2)

    
    mat_cor<- matrix(0, nrow=length(celltypes_1), ncol=length(celltypes_2))

    for( i in 1:length(celltypes_1) ){
        #print(i)
        for( j in 1:length(celltypes_2)){
            celltype_i<- celltypes_1[i]
            celltype_j<- celltypes_2[j]
            # cohort1
            temp1<- lis_1[[celltype_i]]
            colnames(temp1)<- paste0(colnames(temp1), ".cohort1")
            # cohort2
            temp2<- lis_2[[celltype_j]]
            colnames(temp2)<- paste0(colnames(temp2), ".cohort2")
            ggdat<- cbind(temp1, temp2)                    
            mat_cor[i,j]<- cor(ggdat$log2FoldChange.cohort1, ggdat$log2FoldChange.cohort2)
        }
    }

    rownames(mat_cor)<-celltypes_1
    colnames(mat_cor)<-celltypes_2

    ## ordering celltypes 1
    missing<- setdiff(celltypes_order_1, celltypes_1)
    if( length(missing) > 0 ){
        cat("Missing cells 1:", missing, "\n")
    }    
    celltypes_order_1<- intersect(celltypes_order_1, celltypes_1)

    ## ordering celltypes 2
    missing<- setdiff(celltypes_order_2, celltypes_2)
    if( length(missing) > 0 ){
        cat("Missing cells 2:", missing, "\n")
    }
    celltypes_order_2<- intersect(celltypes_order_2, celltypes_2)

    return(mat_cor[celltypes_order_1, celltypes_order_2])   
    
}
# Function to generate correlation heatmaps between DESeq2 (cohort1) and DESeq2 (cohort2)
cor_heatmap_gedi<- function(lis_gedi_1, lis_gedi_2, celltypes_order_1, celltypes_order_2) {
    
    intersect_genes_gedi<- intersect(rownames(lis_gedi_1[[1]]), rownames(lis_gedi_2[[1]]))

    cat("genes intersecting:", length(intersect_genes_gedi), "\n")

    for( i in 1:length(lis_gedi_1) ){
        lis_gedi_1[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_gedi_1[[i]])[intersect_genes_gedi,]
    }

    for( i in 1:length(lis_gedi_2) ){
        lis_gedi_2[[i]]<- data.frame(lis_gedi_2[[i]])[intersect_genes_gedi,]
    }

    mat_cor<- matrix(0, nrow=length(lis_gedi_1), ncol=length(lis_gedi_2))
    
    for( i in 1:length(lis_gedi_1) ){
        for( j in 1:length(lis_gedi_2) ){
            # cohort1
            temp1<- lis_gedi_1[[i]]
            # cohort2
            temp2<- lis_gedi_2[[j]]
            mat_cor[i,j]<- cor(temp1, temp2)
        }
    }
    rownames(mat_cor)<- names(lis_gedi_1)
    colnames(mat_cor)<- names(lis_gedi_2)
    
    ## ordering celltypes 1   
    missing<- setdiff(celltypes_order_1, names(lis_gedi_1))
    if( length(missing) > 0 ){
        cat("Missing cells 1:", missing, "\n")
    }
    celltypes_order_1<- intersect(celltypes_order_1, names(lis_gedi_1))

    missing<- setdiff(celltypes_order_2, names(lis_gedi_2))
    if( length(missing) > 0 ){
        cat("Missing cells 1:", missing, "\n")
    }
    celltypes_order_2<- intersect(celltypes_order_2, names(lis_gedi_2))

    return(mat_cor[celltypes_order_1, celltypes_order_2])

    
}
